01:30:00.080 --> 01:30:01.380
I know you do.

01:30:01.480 --> 01:30:02.891
- I know.
- Ladies and gentlemen,

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:04.900
let me just give you the lowdown
on this next fella's...

01:30:05.000 --> 01:30:07.401
But you are better off without her, son.

01:30:08.320 --> 01:30:10.482
She was never worth a half of you.

01:30:12.080 --> 01:30:14.220
I got a little boy I worry about, too.

01:30:14.320 --> 01:30:16.402
...he's got a new song out there
that he wrote for us.

01:30:31.520 --> 01:30:32.580
Yes, sir.

01:30:32.680 --> 01:30:34.500
I got a brand-new song,
ain't never been aired.

01:30:34.600 --> 01:30:36.540
Ain't never been aired?

01:30:36.640 --> 01:30:38.210
No, but it just might need it.

01:30:38.720 --> 01:30:39.926
Doggone it, Hank!

01:30:40.240 --> 01:30:41.730
All right, boys, let it roll.

01:30:47.320 --> 01:30:51.020
Well, why don't you love me
like you used to do?

01:30:51.120 --> 01:30:54.020
How come you treat me
like a worn-out shoe?

01:30:54.120 --> 01:30:57.380
My hair's still curly
and my eyes are still blue

01:30:57.480 --> 01:31:00.529
Why don't you love me like you used to do?

01:31:00.640 --> 01:31:03.620
I ain't had no lovin'
like a-huggin' and a-kissin'

01:31:03.720 --> 01:31:07.100
In a long, long while

01:31:07.200 --> 01:31:10.340
We don't get nearer or further

01:31:10.440 --> 01:31:13.728
Or closer than a country mile

01:31:14.840 --> 01:31:17.900
Why don't you spark me
like you used to do?

01:31:18.000 --> 01:31:21.260
And say sweet nothings
like you used to coo

01:31:21.360 --> 01:31:23.140
I'm the same old trouble

01:31:23.240 --> 01:31:24.820
That you've always been through

01:31:24.920 --> 01:31:28.180
Why don't you love me like you used to do?

01:31:28.280 --> 01:31:29.327
Don Helms.

01:31:40.920 --> 01:31:42.046
Burt Hale.

01:32:10.600 --> 01:32:14.340
Well, why don't you be
just like you used to be?

01:32:14.440 --> 01:32:17.820
How come you find so many faults with me?

01:32:17.920 --> 01:32:21.340
Somebody's changed
so let me give you a clue

01:32:21.440 --> 01:32:24.020
Why don't you love me like you used to do?

01:32:24.120 --> 01:32:25.660
I ain't had no lovin'

01:32:25.760 --> 01:32:30.561
Like a-huggin' and a-kissin'
in a long, long while

01:32:32.960 --> 01:32:33.900
I just laughed it off.

01:32:34.000 --> 01:32:35.411
I don't know.

01:32:37.000 --> 01:32:38.161
Hey, girl.

01:32:41.720 --> 01:32:42.860
You here with anybody?

01:32:42.960 --> 01:32:43.961
Faron Young.

01:32:44.480 --> 01:32:46.220
Boy guesting up in Shreveport?

01:32:46.320 --> 01:32:47.401
That's him.

01:32:48.320 --> 01:32:50.971
And that's him right over there
behind you.

01:32:52.120 --> 01:32:53.060
Hey, Faron.

01:32:53.160 --> 01:32:54.140
Hank.

01:32:54.240 --> 01:32:56.163
- Good to meet you.
- Good to meet you.

01:32:56.840 --> 01:32:58.001
Billie?

01:32:58.800 --> 01:33:00.006
You gonna marry this girl?

01:33:01.600 --> 01:33:02.780
Well, are you?

01:33:02.880 --> 01:33:04.450
Well, not likely.

01:33:05.240 --> 01:33:07.242
She's far too good-looking for a wife.

01:33:08.080 --> 01:33:10.162
Well, if you ain't gonna marry her,

01:33:11.680 --> 01:33:13.330
ol' Hank just might.

01:33:13.840 --> 01:33:15.604
- Is that right?
- That's right.

01:33:17.200 --> 01:33:18.300
Son.

01:33:18.400 --> 01:33:20.402
I hope I ain't causing you any pain.

01:33:21.240 --> 01:33:22.844
Don't worry about it.

01:33:29.400 --> 01:33:31.084
You're like an angel.

01:33:33.440 --> 01:33:34.700
My two boys over there,

01:33:34.800 --> 01:33:37.167
Alton and Sonny, big fans of yours.

01:33:38.040 --> 01:33:39.220
Pregnant at 16.

01:33:39.320 --> 01:33:40.820
So, Jeri Lynn there.

01:33:40.920 --> 01:33:42.809
Married and pregnant, Mr. Jones.

01:33:43.240 --> 01:33:45.300
Well, I'm not selling her short.

01:33:45.400 --> 01:33:46.731
She is pretty tough.

01:33:47.720 --> 01:33:48.980
I bet she is.

01:33:49.080 --> 01:33:51.740
Nineteen years old,
what the hell do you know?

01:33:51.840 --> 01:33:53.620
Yeah, I could barely tie
my own shoes then.

01:33:53.720 --> 01:33:55.609
Well, heck, I wasn't even wearin' them.

01:33:57.400 --> 01:33:59.050
I like children a lot.

01:33:59.360 --> 01:34:01.020
I got one of my own,

01:34:01.120 --> 01:34:02.884
and my former wife had one, too.

01:34:03.600 --> 01:34:06.580
Well, you're handsome,
talented and love kids.

01:34:06.680 --> 01:34:08.045
How about that, Daddy?

01:34:08.840 --> 01:34:10.888
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:34:22.960 --> 01:34:24.564
- Hey, Ray.
- Hank.

01:34:27.280 --> 01:34:28.281
Bobbie.

01:34:28.680 --> 01:34:29.727
Hank.

01:34:33.560 --> 01:34:34.561
You with him?

01:34:35.040 --> 01:34:36.121
Nope.

01:34:36.680 --> 01:34:37.700
You with him?

01:34:37.800 --> 01:34:39.540
Bobbie, what are you doing here?

01:34:39.640 --> 01:34:40.820
What do you think, Hank?

01:34:40.920 --> 01:34:42.660
- That's nice.
- Thank you.

01:34:42.760 --> 01:34:44.540
Billie, let me handle this, please.

01:34:44.640 --> 01:34:45.980
Bobbie, we got to talk.

01:34:46.080 --> 01:34:47.081
Talk?

01:34:47.640 --> 01:34:48.846
Get her out of here.

01:34:49.200 --> 01:34:50.770
I'm sorry, darling.

01:34:51.360 --> 01:34:52.930
But who do you think you are?

01:34:53.320 --> 01:34:54.820
Well, I was the woman he was gonna marry.

01:34:54.920 --> 01:34:56.380
- Really? Lucky him.
- Billie.

01:34:56.480 --> 01:34:58.660
Maybe you should have told some
of your other girls that, Hank.

01:34:58.760 --> 01:35:00.762
- Bobbie.
- Well, you are right about that, honey.

01:35:00.880 --> 01:35:01.881
Bobbie.

01:35:02.160 --> 01:35:03.340
Billie. Billie!

01:35:03.440 --> 01:35:04.441
Billie!

01:35:05.040 --> 01:35:07.020
Billie, there isn't anybody else,
I swear to God!

01:35:07.120 --> 01:35:08.531
She got it wrong about us, okay?

01:35:08.640 --> 01:35:09.820
They get it that way sometimes.

01:35:09.920 --> 01:35:12.321
"They"?

01:35:13.800 --> 01:35:16.644
Boy, you're a real piece of work,
Hank Williams.

01:35:17.120 --> 01:35:19.282
You know, I may just be
a Bossier City kid,

01:35:19.400 --> 01:35:21.380
but I got enough sense
to know you're trouble,

01:35:21.480 --> 01:35:22.891
and you're gonna tear me up.

01:35:24.880 --> 01:35:25.961
Billie.

01:35:27.000 --> 01:35:29.002
Billie!

01:35:31.200 --> 01:35:34.380
We're gonna have a big ol' time
at the Grand Ole Opry tonight!

01:35:34.480 --> 01:35:36.700
That's right. We got quite a lineup.

01:35:36.800 --> 01:35:39.804
We've got Bob Mayfield,
we've got Minnie Pearl,

01:35:39.920 --> 01:35:42.287
and Hank Williams!

01:35:44.040 --> 01:35:45.860
So, let's put our hands together.

01:35:45.960 --> 01:35:48.804
Let's do a live
and lively rousing welcome.

01:35:59.680 --> 01:36:00.681
Hank?

01:36:06.440 --> 01:36:07.487
Hank.

01:36:10.800 --> 01:36:12.529
Hey, Jim.

01:36:12.840 --> 01:36:13.841
Hank.

01:36:17.920 --> 01:36:20.020
You want something? Cup of coffee?

01:36:20.120 --> 01:36:21.167
No, thanks.

01:36:22.560 --> 01:36:23.766
Where's Ray?

01:36:24.680 --> 01:36:25.886
He moved out.

01:36:29.320 --> 01:36:31.940
I don't want to know where you were
or why you weren't at the show.

01:36:32.040 --> 01:36:33.660
- I'm sorry, J.D.
- I'm sure.

01:36:33.760 --> 01:36:34.980
But sorry don't mean shit.

01:36:35.080 --> 01:36:36.140
We're grown men.

01:36:36.240 --> 01:36:37.260
I see.

01:36:37.360 --> 01:36:39.100
Should I be taking notes on this lesson?

01:36:39.200 --> 01:36:41.980
Opry's a brand
and you're pissing on it, Hank.

01:36:42.080 --> 01:36:44.420
It means something to a lot of people.

01:36:44.520 --> 01:36:46.300
Music, family.

01:36:46.400 --> 01:36:47.606
Money?

01:36:48.440 --> 01:36:50.740
You want to play the artist on me?
All right, then.

01:36:50.840 --> 01:36:54.045
An artist like you, a man who can
make folks forget their troubles,

01:36:54.160 --> 01:36:55.571
you have an obligation.

01:36:58.440 --> 01:37:00.460
You been working me pretty hard, J.D.

01:37:00.560 --> 01:37:04.770
I mean, 100 out of 119 days on the road.

01:37:04.880 --> 01:37:06.769
I don't really need any more obligations.

01:37:06.880 --> 01:37:08.086
Nobody does.

01:37:08.840 --> 01:37:10.980
I'm not trying to be disrespectful, Hank.

01:37:11.080 --> 01:37:12.020
I'm not trying to put you down.

01:37:12.120 --> 01:37:13.100
Don't you worry.

01:37:13.200 --> 01:37:16.180
I gave up giving a shit about what
other people think a long time ago.

01:37:16.280 --> 01:37:17.660
All right, then.

01:37:17.760 --> 01:37:18.921
Here's the deal.

01:37:19.560 --> 01:37:22.260
August 9th in your regular Opry spot,

01:37:22.360 --> 01:37:25.569
and August 10th
an Opry-sponsored show in Knoxville.

01:37:30.040 --> 01:37:31.769
Sure, all right, okay.

01:37:33.040 --> 01:37:34.405
I'm imploring you.

01:37:34.760 --> 01:37:36.683
Don't let me down.

01:37:37.080 --> 01:37:39.526
They'll get their money's worth, sir.

01:37:40.120 --> 01:37:41.121
Okay.

01:37:41.320 --> 01:37:45.291
Of course I mean, Cousin Minnie Pearl!

01:37:51.800 --> 01:37:53.609
Howdy!

01:38:03.160 --> 01:38:05.891
Jambalaya hit number one today,
you know that?

01:38:08.960 --> 01:38:10.380
I had to do it, Red.

01:38:10.480 --> 01:38:12.369
I had to let Hank go.

01:38:32.600 --> 01:38:33.601
Hello?

01:38:34.320 --> 01:38:36.607
Hey, it's Hank.

01:38:36.720 --> 01:38:38.060
Hey, Hank, it's Sonny.

01:38:38.160 --> 01:38:39.900
Hey, Sonny,

01:38:40.000 --> 01:38:41.331
Is your sister around?

01:38:44.920 --> 01:38:47.526
No, I don't know where she is.

01:38:49.800 --> 01:38:52.167
Hey, Sonny, help me out, will you?

01:38:52.360 --> 01:38:53.407
Sure.

01:38:55.000 --> 01:38:56.411
Thanks, man.

01:39:14.200 --> 01:39:15.361
Hello.

01:39:18.360 --> 01:39:20.362
Bobbie, it's me.

01:39:22.800 --> 01:39:24.006
Hey, Hank.

01:39:26.680 --> 01:39:27.886
Hey.

01:39:31.200 --> 01:39:33.580
Listen, I was thinking,
why don't you pack a bag,

01:39:33.680 --> 01:39:36.809
and I'll come by in about a half-hour?

01:39:40.160 --> 01:39:41.525
Where are we going?

01:39:42.800 --> 01:39:44.131
Lake Martin.

01:39:44.520 --> 01:39:46.170
A lodge at Kowaliga Bay.

01:39:46.760 --> 01:39:48.410
It belongs to a pal of mine.

01:39:50.360 --> 01:39:51.441
What do you say?

01:39:57.200 --> 01:39:58.361
Make it an hour.

01:40:17.000 --> 01:40:18.445
Bobbie?

01:40:28.120 --> 01:40:29.281
Bobbie.

01:40:30.440 --> 01:40:32.169
You're drunker than ol' Hank.

01:40:33.680 --> 01:40:35.091
Hank...

01:40:35.920 --> 01:40:37.490
I'm not drunk.

01:40:38.360 --> 01:40:40.601
- No?
- No.

01:40:43.840 --> 01:40:45.490
I'm pregnant.

01:40:48.920 --> 01:40:50.126
What?

01:40:53.120 --> 01:40:55.600
What is it with me?

01:40:57.760 --> 01:41:00.366
Every woman in my life has kids.

01:41:01.440 --> 01:41:03.010
Every one of them.

01:41:05.440 --> 01:41:07.580
Before I even got to them.

01:41:07.680 --> 01:41:08.660
Man.

01:41:08.760 --> 01:41:11.809
You're obviously very
attractive to mothers, Hank.

01:41:25.000 --> 01:41:26.525
Jesus, Bobbie.

01:41:28.320 --> 01:41:29.401
You're pregnant.

01:41:33.520 --> 01:41:35.045
We could get married.

01:41:37.160 --> 01:41:39.561
Baby, you don't want to marry me.

01:41:41.280 --> 01:41:42.406
I will.

01:41:42.960 --> 01:41:44.246
That's different.

01:41:48.440 --> 01:41:51.683
Boy, I'm a professional
at making a mess of things.

01:41:55.280 --> 01:41:56.361
Hank,

01:41:57.680 --> 01:42:00.580
if we got married, things would be easier.

01:42:00.680 --> 01:42:02.364
They'd be more stable.

01:42:03.400 --> 01:42:05.100
And just think,

01:42:05.200 --> 01:42:07.202
we'd have this little one right here.

01:42:11.200 --> 01:42:12.361
Bobbie.

01:42:14.520 --> 01:42:16.170
I love you.

01:42:20.200 --> 01:42:22.248
But not like that.

01:42:26.760 --> 01:42:27.807
Not...

01:42:28.960 --> 01:42:30.371
Not that way.

01:42:40.960 --> 01:42:43.281
'Sides, I'm gonna marry Billie Jean.

01:42:46.240 --> 01:42:47.401
She know that?

01:42:50.880 --> 01:42:52.450
Not exactly.

01:42:55.880 --> 01:42:57.484
Listen, darlin'.

01:42:59.560 --> 01:43:02.450
I'm gonna look after this little baby.

01:43:05.520 --> 01:43:07.124
I'll send you money,

01:43:08.280 --> 01:43:10.282
and I'll be its papa, even.

01:43:13.600 --> 01:43:15.602
There ain't gonna be no marriage.

01:43:25.440 --> 01:43:28.444
Hank, you are really screwed up.

01:43:30.880 --> 01:43:31.961
I know.

01:43:33.640 --> 01:43:36.220
I pulled every string

01:43:36.320 --> 01:43:38.220
to get him back where he started,

01:43:38.320 --> 01:43:40.380
the Hayride in Louisiana.

01:43:40.480 --> 01:43:42.660
It wouldn't be the same money or exposure,

01:43:42.760 --> 01:43:44.380
but at least he wouldn't be idle.

01:43:44.480 --> 01:43:45.900
Hank idle, damn.

01:43:46.000 --> 01:43:49.340
Before long, he had
a Nashville showgirl with child.

01:43:49.440 --> 01:43:52.820
And shortly after that,
he married Billie Jean Jones

01:43:52.920 --> 01:43:55.810
in the City Auditorium, New Orleans.

01:44:19.280 --> 01:44:22.700
It's not just my back, baby.

01:44:22.800 --> 01:44:23.801
I feel...

01:44:25.760 --> 01:44:27.660
I feel like my chest is,

01:44:27.760 --> 01:44:30.445
like, getting jumped on.

01:44:57.040 --> 01:44:58.060
Who are you?

01:44:58.160 --> 01:45:00.481
LeBeau, the promoter.

01:45:02.280 --> 01:45:03.420
And you?

01:45:03.520 --> 01:45:04.965
Dr. Marshall.

01:45:06.400 --> 01:45:08.100
What kind of doctor?

01:45:08.200 --> 01:45:10.248
I specialize in alcoholism.

01:45:11.760 --> 01:45:12.900
What does that mean?

01:45:13.000 --> 01:45:14.540
What you got, Doc?

01:45:14.640 --> 01:45:16.244
What's the man have?

01:45:17.240 --> 01:45:19.481
It means I've been there and back, ma'am,

01:45:20.000 --> 01:45:23.129
and I will help Mr. Williams
to a speedy recovery.

01:45:25.480 --> 01:45:27.482
Let the man in!

01:45:44.600 --> 01:45:46.602
It will be better, son.

01:45:56.240 --> 01:45:57.460
Chloral hydrate.

01:45:57.560 --> 01:46:01.140
So powerful, they use it
to sedate circus animals.

01:46:01.240 --> 01:46:03.100
It's never supposed to be
administered with alcohol

01:46:03.200 --> 01:46:08.300
or to someone with a heart condition,
which Hank likely had.

01:46:08.400 --> 01:46:10.020
Marshall,

01:46:10.120 --> 01:46:14.460
his diploma was from the Chicago University
of Applied Sciences and Arts.

01:46:14.560 --> 01:46:18.246
He bought it off a salesman
at a gas station for $25.

01:46:20.440 --> 01:46:24.240
And then Hank called me
and told me he was in Marshall's care.

01:46:37.680 --> 01:46:39.409
How you doing, son?

01:46:43.000 --> 01:46:45.162
How long we got left?

01:46:45.600 --> 01:46:46.540
We can be done, Hank.

01:46:46.640 --> 01:46:48.005
Just call it a day.

01:46:57.680 --> 01:46:59.364
I got something

01:47:00.120 --> 01:47:02.009
I want to run past you.

01:47:03.160 --> 01:47:04.571
You sure?

01:47:11.120 --> 01:47:15.762
Your cheatin' heart

01:47:18.200 --> 01:47:21.522
Will make you weep

01:47:24.920 --> 01:47:30.245
You'll cry and cry

01:47:30.960 --> 01:47:34.760
And try to sleep

01:47:36.360 --> 01:47:40.410
But sleep won't come

01:47:42.000 --> 01:47:46.085
The whole night through

01:47:47.200 --> 01:47:51.842
Your cheatin' heart

01:47:52.560 --> 01:47:56.485
Will tell on you

01:47:58.040 --> 01:48:03.180
When tears come down

01:48:03.280 --> 01:48:07.444
Like falling rain

01:48:08.680 --> 01:48:14.100
You'll toss around

01:48:14.200 --> 01:48:18.603
And call my name

01:48:19.400 --> 01:48:22.847
You'll walk the floor

01:48:24.880 --> 01:48:29.044
The way I do

01:48:30.360 --> 01:48:35.730
Your cheatin' heart

01:48:38.160 --> 01:48:44.202
Will tell on you

01:48:58.560 --> 01:48:59.900
Hey,

01:49:00.000 --> 01:49:01.411
I heard you got a new toy,

01:49:02.160 --> 01:49:03.340
It's a choo-choo train.

01:49:03.440 --> 01:49:05.340
Are you gonna play with me?

01:49:05.440 --> 01:49:08.091
I'll be right there just as soon as I can.

01:49:10.640 --> 01:49:12.900
You know how much I miss you,
don't you, Bocephus?

01:49:13.000 --> 01:49:15.540
Than all the ants on the sidewalks,

01:49:15.640 --> 01:49:18.325
and all the leaves in the trees.

01:49:23.080 --> 01:49:24.047
That's right.

01:49:24.160 --> 01:49:25.780
Hey, baby, can I talk to Daddy?

01:49:25.880 --> 01:49:27.245
Thank you.

01:49:27.640 --> 01:49:29.540
Hey, Hank? We got to go now.

01:49:29.640 --> 01:49:32.246
It's getting past his bedtime,
and I don't want him getting worked up.

01:49:33.120 --> 01:49:35.700
Audrey, why don't you
bring him up to Shreveport this weekend?

01:49:35.800 --> 01:49:37.290
Well, that won't work out.

01:49:37.920 --> 01:49:39.331
Well, why not?

01:49:39.880 --> 01:49:41.980
I mean, it'd just be for the Saturday,

01:49:42.080 --> 01:49:43.570
You could leave him here and,

01:49:43.680 --> 01:49:45.887
you know, we'll bring him back.

01:49:46.240 --> 01:49:48.083
Well, we got plans Saturday.

01:49:48.960 --> 01:49:50.180
Well, how about Sunday, then?

01:49:50.280 --> 01:49:51.691
No, that won't work.

01:49:52.520 --> 01:49:54.522
We're just gonna have to find
a better time, okay?

01:49:55.600 --> 01:49:56.820
So, I'm gonna talk to you later.

01:49:56.920 --> 01:49:58.365
Okay, hon? Bye.

01:50:42.400 --> 01:50:44.420
The first task of the new administration

01:50:44.520 --> 01:50:46.841
will be to review and reexamine...

01:50:51.600 --> 01:50:54.300
...we have a time-out
existing on the playing field

01:50:54.400 --> 01:50:56.402
on the part
of the University of Alabama...

01:51:02.360 --> 01:51:03.566
Do you have to?

01:51:06.560 --> 01:51:08.130
Yeah, I kind of do.

01:51:19.440 --> 01:51:21.044
Well, honey,

01:51:22.880 --> 01:51:25.360
I'm real glad you're skipping
some of them dates.

01:51:26.760 --> 01:51:28.762
Taking some time.

01:51:30.760 --> 01:51:33.331
And I'm real glad
we're getting out of Shreveport.

01:51:34.440 --> 01:51:35.620
But to tell you the truth,

01:51:35.720 --> 01:51:38.200
I don't really want to see your mother.

01:51:38.960 --> 01:51:40.086
I know that.

01:51:41.760 --> 01:51:44.240
Still, at least,
she'll be happy to see me.

01:51:45.120 --> 01:51:47.646
Lately, people see me coming,
they want to cross the street.

01:51:48.120 --> 01:51:49.804
Well, that's just not true.

01:51:55.040 --> 01:51:56.405
I'm sorry, baby.

01:51:58.120 --> 01:51:59.531
For what?

01:52:03.320 --> 01:52:04.765
Everything.

01:52:08.080 --> 01:52:10.082
A.V Bamford had booked Hank

01:52:10.200 --> 01:52:13.647
for two dates at the end of December.

01:52:14.320 --> 01:52:16.740
New Year's Eve in Charleston,
West Virginia,

01:52:16.840 --> 01:52:19.100
New Year's Day in Canton, Ohio.

01:52:19.200 --> 01:52:21.487
Hank looked around

01:52:21.800 --> 01:52:25.168
for someone to drive him in his own car.

01:52:26.120 --> 01:52:30.340
And when he couldn't find any friends
to take him up on that,

01:52:30.440 --> 01:52:34.260
he called a buddy of his at
Lee Street Taxi in Montgomery.

01:52:34.360 --> 01:52:36.169
And that fella

01:52:36.680 --> 01:52:38.500
got his 17-year-old son,

01:52:38.600 --> 01:52:41.700
Charles Carr, to do the job.

01:52:41.800 --> 01:52:45.122
Charles was a freshman
at Auburn on holiday break.

01:53:02.760 --> 01:53:03.940
Can you take care of that for me?

01:53:04.040 --> 01:53:05.246
Yes, sir.

01:53:07.480 --> 01:53:09.289
Be careful with that, Charles.

01:53:22.800 --> 01:53:24.450
Come here, baby.

01:53:31.040 --> 01:53:33.327
I'll call you when I get up to Charleston.

01:53:33.760 --> 01:53:36.127
How come I can't come?

01:53:39.560 --> 01:53:42.260
Go back to Shreveport,
I'll meet you in a couple days.

01:53:42.360 --> 01:53:43.725
You don't have to stay.

01:53:44.960 --> 01:53:47.770
I don't see the big deal, me coming along.

01:53:48.240 --> 01:53:49.526
Well,

01:53:50.960 --> 01:53:52.724
it's a long-ass trip.

01:53:54.080 --> 01:53:55.570
And, truthfully,

01:53:57.760 --> 01:53:59.603
we might get real sick of each other.

01:53:59.960 --> 01:54:01.644
You might end up going at me, right?

01:54:20.520 --> 01:54:22.522
One more for luck, huh?

01:54:27.080 --> 01:54:29.606
- Watch your head, Mr. Williams.
- Thank you, sir.

01:54:38.960 --> 01:54:40.780
What are you smiling about?

01:54:40.880 --> 01:54:44.168
Well, another reason
I think you shouldn't come,

01:54:45.680 --> 01:54:47.330
I could use the leg room.

01:54:49.600 --> 01:54:51.500
Drive safe, Charles.

01:54:51.600 --> 01:54:55.082
He's a real SOB, but I think I love him.

01:54:55.760 --> 01:54:57.330
Yes, ma'am.

01:54:58.800 --> 01:55:00.802
Listen to the boss, Charles.

01:55:08.200 --> 01:55:09.770
I'll see you in Louisiana, darlin'.

01:55:13.840 --> 01:55:15.251
Happy New Year.

01:56:21.240 --> 01:56:22.890
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:56:24.320 --> 01:56:28.086
I've been in show business
for almost 20 years.

01:56:31.320 --> 01:56:32.731
But today,

01:56:33.600 --> 01:56:36.843
will be the most difficult task
I've ever had to perform.

01:56:41.200 --> 01:56:42.804
This morning,

01:56:43.080 --> 01:56:46.607
on his way to Canton to do this show,

01:56:49.120 --> 01:56:51.521
Hank Williams died in his car.

01:57:03.440 --> 01:57:07.968
I wandered so aimless

01:57:08.760 --> 01:57:12.924
Life filled with sin

01:57:13.760 --> 01:57:17.140
I wouldn't let my

01:57:17.240 --> 01:57:20.244
Dear Savior in

01:57:21.920 --> 01:57:24.900
Then Jesus came like

01:57:25.000 --> 01:57:28.243
A stranger in the night

01:57:29.080 --> 01:57:32.140
Praise the Lord

01:57:32.240 --> 01:57:35.130
I saw the light

01:57:35.800 --> 01:57:38.849
I saw the light

01:57:39.080 --> 01:57:42.380
I saw the light

01:57:42.480 --> 01:57:45.780
No more darkness

01:57:45.880 --> 01:57:48.804
No more night

01:57:49.320 --> 01:57:52.540
Now I'm so happy

01:57:52.640 --> 01:57:55.700
No sorrow in sight

01:57:55.800 --> 01:57:57.500
Praise the Lord...

01:57:57.600 --> 01:58:00.100
Montgomery Alabama,

01:58:00.200 --> 01:58:02.931
January 4th, 1953.

01:58:04.000 --> 01:58:06.580
Hank Williams laid to rest in Dixie.

01:58:06.680 --> 01:58:09.860
I saw the light...

01:58:09.960 --> 01:58:12.300
The top singer-songwriter died tragically

01:58:12.400 --> 01:58:14.243
of severe heart damage.

01:58:15.120 --> 01:58:17.248
He was 29 years old.

01:58:17.920 --> 01:58:19.940
In only six years of recording,

01:58:20.040 --> 01:58:22.060
he had a remarkable 36 hit songs

01:58:22.160 --> 01:58:25.004
and sold over 11 million records.

01:58:26.560 --> 01:58:31.060
Fans, friends and family
gave the boy from Mount Olive

01:58:31.160 --> 01:58:33.580
the state's largest send-off ever,

01:58:33.680 --> 01:58:35.460
accompanied by the mournful sounds

01:58:35.560 --> 01:58:39.100
of his buddies' steel guitars
and weeping fiddles.

01:58:39.200 --> 01:58:40.900
No more darkness

01:58:41.000 --> 01:58:43.765
No more night...

